To save the PDF document to a Firestore collection, you can use the `cloud_firestore` package. First, you need to add the package to your `pubspec.yaml` file if you haven't already:
```yaml
dependencies:
  cloud_firestore: ^3.1.7
```
Then, import the `cloud_firestore` package in your code:
```dart
import 'package:cloud_firestore/cloud_firestore.dart';
```
After that, you can create a function that saves the document to Firestore:
```dart
Future<void> saveDocumentToFirestore({
  required String userId,
  required String documentName,
  required String pdfUrl,
  required DateTime timeCreated,
}) async {
  final userReference = FirebaseFirestore.instance
      .collection('Users')
      .doc(userId);

  await FirebaseFirestore.instance.collection('docs').add({
    'user_reference': userReference,
    'document-name': documentName,
    'pdf_url': pdfUrl,
    'time_created': timeCreated,
  });
}
```
Now, call this function in your `ractemplate` function after uploading the PDF to Firebase Storage:
```dart
// Save the file to Firebase Storage
final downloadUrl = await uploadData(storagePath, pdfSaved);

