1. Add a function to your React component that parses the Additional Notes text and extracts the Acceptance Criteria in Gherkin format. You can use a regular expression to match the text following the "Acceptance Criteria" subheading and extract the lines of text that start with "Given," "When," or "Then."
2. Create state variables for each of the Acceptance Criteria data fields in your React component. You can initialize these state variables to an empty string.
3. In the function that extracts the Acceptance Criteria from the Additional Notes text, set the state variables for each of the Acceptance Criteria data fields to the corresponding text.
4. Render the Acceptance Criteria data fields in your component, using the state variables as the values for each field.

Here's a step-by-step guide to implementing this in your React/Ruby on Rails web application:

1. In your React component, add a function that parses the Additional Notes text and extracts the Acceptance Criteria in Gherkin format. Here's an example implementation:
```javascript
function extractAcceptanceCriteria(text) {
  const regex = /Acceptance Criteria([\s\S]*?)\n\n/g;
  const matches = regex.exec(text);
  if (matches && matches.length > 1) {
    const criteriaText = matches[1];
    const givenRegex = /^Given (.*)$/gm;
    const whenRegex = /^When (.*)$/gm;
    const thenRegex = /^Then (.*)$/gm;
    const givenMatches = [...criteriaText.matchAll(givenRegex)];
    const whenMatches = [...criteriaText.matchAll(whenRegex)];
    const thenMatches = [...criteriaText.matchAll(thenRegex)];
    const given = givenMatches.map(match => match[1]).join('\n');
    const when = whenMatches.map(match => match[1]).join('\n');
    const then = thenMatches.map(match => match[1]).join('\n');
    return { given, when, then };
  } else {
    return { given: '', when: '', then: '' };
  }
}
```
This function uses a regular expression to match the text following the "Acceptance Criteria" subheading and extract the lines of text that start with "Given," "When," or "Then." It then returns an object with properties for each of the Acceptance Criteria data fields.

